::DarkMouse::

She slowly started to come around.  She had a big knot on her head 
from where she hit the tree branch.   She was still laying there, and 
seeing with blurred vision from the impact.  She had hit that thing 
rather hard.  She rolled over on her side and groaned. "Oh cripes, 
where did that brick wall come from?  It just ran out in front of 
me." She slowly got up to her knees.  She transformed into bot mode 
and looked around.  She had only been out for a few minutes, but that 
was time lost that she could have used to run away with.  She looked 
around and rubbed her eyes.  her optics were stilled a little fuzzy, 
but she could see something, something bigger than her, running 
towards her.  She turned and went to run, when she hit the tree 
branch again.  She fell down and groaned. "Gee, you'd think the 
Matrix wasn't on my side today."  She got up again and this time, she 
ducked under the branch.  But the bot was not almost on top of her.  
She just ran, vision blurred still, she just ran through the forest.
